    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The compiler tries to avoid generating getters that will return big amounts of data in one go and be very expensive (maybe even unusable). When you define your own getter, it's still a problem but it's up to you to decide what to do about that, the compiler won't stop you there.",
